    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Between this commit\n\nc31abb8e7cde38b8d664338b39d9c8d51ccd28e7\n\nAnd this commit\n\nb4d65bce97795438ab6e1974b3672c17a4865e3c\n\n`vim.defaulttable()` is no longer useable\n\nThis used to work.\n\n```lua\n-- vim.defaulttable() will allow us to set values in the `servers` table\n-- like a nix attribute set without explicitly creating each internal table.\nlocal servers = vim.defaulttable()\n\n-- most don't need much configuration\n-- servers.gopls = {}\n-- servers.html = {}\n\n-- but you can provide some if you want to!\nservers.lua_ls.settings.Lua = {\n  formatters = {\n    ignoreComments = true,\n  },\n  signatureHelp = { enabled = true },\n  diagnostics = {\n    globals = { 'vim' },\n    disable = { 'missing-fields' },\n  },\n}\n\nlocal lspconfig = require('lspconfig')\nlspconfig.util.default_config = vim.tbl_extend(\n  \"force\",\n  lspconfig.util.default_config,\n  {\n    capabilities = vim.lsp.protocol.make_client_capabilities(),\n    on_attach = function(_, bufnr)\n    end,\n  }\n)\n-- set up the servers to be loaded on the appropriate filetypes!\nfor server_name, cfg in pairs(servers) do\n  lspconfig[server_name].setup(cfg or {})\nend\n```\n\nand now it does not and I need to do\n\n```lua\n-- vim.defaulttable() will allow us to set values in the `servers` table\n-- like a nix attribute set without explicitly creating each internal table.\nlocal servers = {}\n\n-- most don't need much configuration\n-- servers.gopls = {}\n-- servers.html = {}\n\n-- but you can provide some if you want to!\nservers.lua_ls = {\n  settings = {\n    Lua = {\n      formatters = {\n        ignoreComments = true,\n      },\n      signatureHelp = { enabled = true },\n      diagnostics = {\n        globals = { 'vim' },\n        disable = { 'missing-fields' },\n      },\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nlocal lspconfig = require('lspconfig')\nlspconfig.util.default_config = vim.tbl_extend(\n  \"force\",\n  lspconfig.util.default_config,\n  {\n    capabilities = vim.lsp.protocol.make_client_capabilities(),\n    on_attach = function(_, bufnr)\n    end,\n  }\n)\n-- set up the servers to be loaded on the appropriate filetypes!\nfor server_name, cfg in pairs(servers) do\n  lspconfig[server_name].setup(cfg or {})\nend\n```\n\nThe behavior is that it does an infinite loop on startup with first example in a `plugin/something.lua` file in the config, and does not with the second, whereas previously, both worked.",
